  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All six QoI comparisons satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% difference, E/uval <1.96). Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved gradation 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by the regulatory precedent of ASTM F1717 as an accepted test standard and the consistency of results across two independent laboratories. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission decision. Aleatory uncertainty across specimens is discussed qualitatively in the test reports and partially characterized through UQ artifacts linked to selected validation results; the assessment team concluded that residual uncharacterized aleatory uncertainty does not materially affect the accept/reject decision given the conservative acceptance bounds employed.",
